  "commentary": "With SPX at 6598.26 sitting just below the massive 6600 GEX flip strike (59.4B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above 6600 while providing support on dips toward the 6595 level (25.6B positive gamma). The PIN regime combined with the wall break and GEX surge signals dealers are actively hedging heavy option flow, creating a strong gravitational pull back toward the 6598-6600 range. Watch 6600 as the critical resistance where dealer selling intensifies, and 6595/6590 as key support levels where dealer buying should emerge.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pinned around 6600 with limited upside breakout potential.",
